Note. 
<bibRefCitation author="Truxal, F. S." box="[219,374,1907,1934]" pageId="16" pageNumber="61" pagination="1351 - 1523" refId="ref22380" refString="Truxal, F. S. (1953) A revision of the genus Buenoa (Hemiptera, Notonectidae). University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 35, 1351 - 1523." type="journal article" year="1953">Truxal (1953)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authority="(Champion, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Champion" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[485,869,1907,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Notonectidae" genus="Buenoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis box="[485,658,1907,1933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="61">Buenoa pallens</emphasis>
(Champion, 1901)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[937,998,1907,1933]" name="Chile" pageId="16" pageNumber="61">Chile</collectingCountry>
based on specimens collected by H. H. Keifer in Magdalena Island, on 
<date box="[514,675,1943,1970]" pageId="16" pageNumber="61" value="1925-05-19">May 19, 1925</date>
. During this period, Keifer was collecting in Islas Marías, 
<collectingCountry box="[1344,1432,1943,1969]" name="Mexico" pageId="16" pageNumber="61">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, not in 
<collectingCountry box="[224,285,1979,2005]" name="Chile" pageId="16" pageNumber="61">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Van Doesburg, P. H." box="[300,569,1979,2005]" pageId="16" pageNumber="61" refId="ref22413" refString="Van Doesburg, P. H. (1968) A revision of the New World species of Dysdercus Guerin Meneville (Heteroptera, Pyrrhocoridae). E. J. Brill, Leiden, 234 pp." type="book" year="1968">van Doesburg 1968: 72</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kelsey, L. P." box="[580,783,1979,2005]" pageId="16" pageNumber="61" refId="ref18433" refString="Kelsey, L. P. (1969) A revision of the Scenopinidae (Diptera) of the World. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C., 124 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 16405" type="book" year="1969">Kelsey 1969: 142</bibRefCitation>
). Becuse this is the only record of the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1369,1432,1979,2005]" name="Chile" pageId="16" pageNumber="61">Chile</collectingCountry>
, we consider that it does not occur in the country.
</paragraph>
